densityFilter

public static BinList densityFilter(BinList binList,
                                    double lowThreshold,
                                    double highThreshold,
                                    double density,
                                    int regionSize)
                             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Applies a filter on a BinList selecting region where there is at least the specified density of bins above and under specified thresholds The result is returned in a new BinList.

Parameters:
binList -
lowThreshold - select values above this threshold
highThreshold - select values under this threshold
density - minimum density of windows above and under the thresholds for a region to be selected (percentage btw 0 and 1)
regionSize - size of the region (in number of bins)
Returns:
a new BinList with only the selected windows
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the low threshold is greater than the high
